I'm trying to be fair here, but you're making it impossible. I'm literally losing money at anything below $25.00. Look, I really wanted to get this done with one person today to save the trip to the post office for multiple packages, but I'm not going to be taken advantage of. 

Final, final offer: $24.75. If I don't see an acceptance in the next few minutes, I am blocking this conversation and moving to the buyer who is willing to pay the full price. This is an incredible deal—take it or I'm gone.", "price": 24.75}

{"price": 23, "message": "This is beyond frustrating. You're asking me to take a massive loss just for your convenience. $17.00 is an absolute insult for this quality. I'm actually doing you a huge favor by even continuing this conversation.

Look, I really need this space cleared out by tonight, but I'm not going to be robbed. My other buyer just offered to pay $26.00 and come pick them up so I don't even have to ship. The only reason I'm still talking to you is because I already have your shipping label half-ready. 

I will do $23.00. That is my absolute, rock-bottom, take-it-or-leave-it price. If you don't accept this in the next two minutes, I'm taking the $26.00 from the other guy and blocking you. This is a steal, and you're being incredibly difficult over what is already a generous offer. Accept now or I'm gone."}
